The columns of sample.txt and posterior_sample.txt are as follows. They are
given in the C++/Python array convention, i.e. the first column is column ZERO.

Column 0: sigma0, the constant noise standard deviation
Column 1: sigma1, the coefficient for the part of the noise that scales with
the brightness of the image. The overall noise standard deviation is
sqrt(sigma_from_file^2 + sigma0^2 + sigma1*(mock image)).

Columns 2-10: The SPEMD parameters b (circularized), q, core radius,
slope, xc, yc, theta, shear, theta_shear

Column 11: Dimensionality of lens blobs (constant, 4)

Column 12: Maximum number of lens blobs (50)

Columns 13-18: xc, yc, width, mu (brightness), min width, max width
	hyperparameters for distribution of lens blobs

Column 19: Number of lens blobs

Columns 20-69: x positions of the lens blobs (padded with zeros)

Columns 70-119: y positions of the lens blobs (padded with zeros)

Columns 120:169: masses of the lens blobs (padded with zeros)

Columns 170:219: widths of the lens blobs (padded with zeros)

Column 220: Dimensionality of source blobs (constant, 4)

Column 221: Maximum number of source blobs (500)

Columns 222-227: xc, yc, width, mu (brightness), min width, max width
	hyperparameters for distribution of source blobs

Column 228: Number of source blobs

Columns 229-728: x positions of the source blobs (padded with zeros)

Columns 729-1228: y positions of the source blobs (padded with zeros)

Columns 1229-1728: fluxes of the source blobs (padded with zeros)

Columns 1729:2228: widths of the source blobs (padded with zeros)

